.TH PLATES 1 "June 2026" "PLATES" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
plates \- local render-only command-template system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B plates
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B PLATES
loads reusable YAML command templates called plates, resolves options from
pantry values, workspace values, option defaults, environment variables, and
local secrets, then prints rendered command text for manual review.
.PP
PLATES is render-only. It does not execute rendered commands.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Variables and State
.TP
.B show pantry
Show global pantry variables.
.TP
.B show workspace
Show active workspace variables.
.TP
.B show options
Show required and optional options for the loaded plate.
.TP
.B set <key> <value>
Set a variable in the active workspace.
.TP
.B setg <key> <value>
Set a global pantry variable.
.TP
.B workspace <name>
Switch to or create a workspace.
.SS Plate Usage
.TP
.B list plates
List available plates by category.
.TP
.B search plates <query>
Search plate names, categories, descriptions, tags, and options.
.TP
.B use <plate>
Load a plate by name or category/name.
.TP
.B info
Show loaded plate metadata and a template preview.
.TP
.B ll
Alias for
.BR info .
.TP
.B render
Render the loaded plate.
.TP
.B r
Alias for
.BR render .
.TP
.B run
Alias for
.BR render .
This command renders only and does not execute output.
.TP
.B clear plate
Unload the current plate.
.SS Forge Mode
.TP
.B forge
.TQ
.B use forge
Enter interactive Forge Mode.
.PP
Preferred Forge option commands are:
.BR add_option
and
.BR add_optional_option .
The older
.BR add_var
and
.BR add_optional_var
forms remain aliases.
.SS Rack / Packs
.TP
.B show rack
Show rack summary.
.TP
.B show tags
Show tag counts.
.TP
.B show category <name>
Show plates in a category.
.TP
.B pack list
List exported and imported packs.
.TP
.B pack export <name>
Export the rack as a pack.
.TP
.B pack inspect <path>
Inspect a pack without importing it.
.TP
.B pack validate <path>
Validate a pack.
.TP
.B pack import <path>
Import a pack.
.SS Output
.TP
.B copy
Copy the most recent rendered output to the clipboard.
.TP
.B save output [filename]
Save the most recent rendered output.
.TP
.B history
Show recent rendered outputs.
.TP
.B export markdown
.TQ
.B export json
.TQ
.B export yaml
Export the most recent render.
.SS Guides and Utility
.TP
.B init
Create data directories and default config if needed.
.TP
.B guide
List built-in guide topics.
.TP
.B guide <topic>
Show a built-in guide topic.
.TP
.B shell clear
Clear the terminal screen.
.TP
.B config show
Show configuration.
.TP
.B config set <key> <value>
Set a supported configuration value.
.TP
.B help
Show shell help.
.TP
.B exit
.TQ
.B quit
Exit the shell.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I data/config.yaml
Application config.
.TP
.I data/pantry/globals.yaml
Global pantry variables.
.TP
.I data/workspaces/<name>.yaml
Workspace variables.
.TP
.I data/rack/**/*.yml
Plate YAML files.
.TP
.I data/output/
Render history and saved output.
.TP
.I data/packs/
Pack import/export data.
.TP
.I data/secrets/secrets.yaml
Local plaintext secret store.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
init
workspace devhub
set target 10.129.202.242
set workdir C:\\Users\\BOB\\code\\boxes\\devhub
setg my_ip 10.10.14.3
list plates
use scanning/nmap_full_tcp
info
show options
render
history
save output nmap_full_tcp.txt
.fi
.PP
Use the render-only alias:
.PP
.nf
run
.fi
.SH SAFETY
PLATES does not execute rendered commands, Forge draft content, pack contents,
or shell output. Review rendered text before copying it into another terminal.
.PP
Secrets are masked in normal displays and redacted in render history by default,
but the local secret store is plaintext.
